# Root Cause Analysis First

When handling bugs, regressions, or failing tests, fix the underlying cause instead of applying a temporary patch.

## Required behavior

- Reproduce and understand the issue before editing code.
- Identify and explain the root cause in implementation notes.
- Prefer the smallest durable fix that removes the cause of failure.
- Avoid workaround-only changes (quick patches, band-aids, TODO deferrals) unless explicitly requested.
- If a temporary mitigation is unavoidable, clearly label it as temporary, explain risk, and include a follow-up task to remove it.

## Verification expectations

- Add or update a test that fails before the fix and passes after it when practical.
- Confirm related flows still work to avoid regressions.

## Example

```text
Bad: "Add null check here so it stops crashing."
Good: "Find why null is produced, fix that source path, and keep a guard only as defense-in-depth."
```
